item.title: How to dump hidden children interface ids
item.dc:creator: @silabsoft RuneAgent
item.description:
@silabsoft wrote:

This is a client side edit. you can find out what exactly this dumps by looking http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,106596.0.html

open up class9

add import java.io.*;

add public static PrintStream write;

addpublic static void write(Class9 class9){ if(class9.aBoolean266){ write.println("Hidden Child Interface Id: "+class9.anInt250); write.println("Parent Interface Id: "+class9.anInt236); write.println(); } }

in method205 add this at the bottom just above the while(true)write(class9);

in method205 add this before the loop near the top of the method is fine try{ write = new PrintStream(new File("Hidden Interface.txt")); }catch(Exception e){}
